MAIL CHECK RECEIVE

The commands used by the World Postal Service (WPS) are MAIL, CHECK, and
RECEIVE.  These commands can only be used while in an Official WPS Post
Office.

To write mail to Whisper:
^c< 10P 10M > mail whisper^n

To check and see if you have any mail waiting:
^c< 10P 10M > check^n

To ask the Postmaster to give you your mail, if you have any waiting:
^c< 10P 10M > receive^n

